{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"babc5a37-ebee-42ac-830b-1bacceeb28b4","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\nHere are your main options for analyzing a `.dmp` file:\n\n**1. `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform, easiest)**\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <your-file>.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the REPL:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**2. `lldb` with SOS (Linux/macOS)**\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core <your-file>.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `dso`, etc.\n\n**3. WinDbg / Visual Studio (Windows)**\nOpen the dump directly and use the SOS debugging extension.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and walk you through the analysis interactively? If so, share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79e30c7f-b5b6-40e3-9435-5a40bcabc93b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"204B:2A854:791F81:8CA815:69F0139A"},"id":"84eb7cbe-0e93-4dc0-9eb7-578a9292b87d","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:55:50.729Z","parentId":"e15eda09-06ce-4e7c-9f3a-b39fc2d5f678"}
